{"info": {"author": "Andrew Leech", "author_email": "andrew@alelec.net", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "================\npip-system-certs\n================\n\nThis package patches pip and requests at runtime to use certificates from the default system store (rather than the bundled certs ca).\n\nThis will allow pip to verify tls/ssl connections to servers who's cert is trusted by your system install.\n\nSimply install with::\n\n  pip install pip_system_certs\n\nand pip should trust your https sites if your host os does.\n\nThis also extends to all direct uses of the requests library (and other packages that use requests)\n\n\nAcknowledgements\n----------------\nThe method of patching at runtime is built from the autowrapt module: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/autowrapt", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/alelec/pip-system-certs", "keywords": "", "license": "BSD", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pip-system-certs", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pip-system-certs/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pip-system-certs/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://gitlab.com/alelec/pip-system-certs"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pip-system-certs/2.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=2.7.9, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "summary": "Live patches pip to use system certs by default", "version": "2.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>This package patches pip and requests at runtime to use certificates from the default system store (rather than the bundled certs ca).</p>\n<p>This will allow pip to verify tls/ssl connections to servers who\u2019s cert is trusted by your system install.</p>\n<p>Simply install with:</p>\n<pre>pip install pip_system_certs\n</pre>\n<p>and pip should trust your https sites if your host os does.</p>\n<p>This also extends to all direct uses of the requests library (and other packages that use requests)</p>\n<div id=\"acknowledgements\">\n<h2>Acknowledgements</h2>\n<p>The method of patching at runtime is built from the autowrapt module: <a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/autowrapt\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://pypi.python.org/pypi/autowrapt</a></p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4388655, "releases": {"1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a3bfb0a7e02c8fd86e3b282a89919647", "sha256": "65945444787299f5ab952c8a8b510786bc8d86e76cbf67a07d62947da296e011"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pip_system_certs-1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "a3bfb0a7e02c8fd86e3b282a89919647", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=2.7.9, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "size": 4363, "upload_time": "2018-03-21T04:35:46", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-03-21T04:35:46.979396Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/30/d5/4528ba2e49b8e99adc34ac1dd1a7ddf8096c5dd2d3b93dbd0a720384725e/pip_system_certs-1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5c70261364aa272352ecbdb11212173a", "sha256": "cd6e0449e237174fbe554484eb6acce14a91d132037b7e59086c3bc120441940"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pip_system_certs-1.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5c70261364aa272352ecbdb11212173a", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=2.7.9, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "size": 4369, "upload_time": "2018-03-21T04:46:44", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-03-21T04:46:44.633613Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7e/13/dcac94744db671724e22c6ad4f49e5b64d8cdecff539e1a3669db32055cc/pip_system_certs-1.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f19864a2739a3b3c8a60b82142c62dcc", "sha256": "469e15c5ab972080a7683e469fd3c6f12d2af91f3f1a76a4ce049f2dd0a79779"}, "downloads